,(240,'Tempered Glass (6)','https://member.asianproducts.com/images/pmimage/6/P13680802540950659m.jpg?1368080525',240,'<p>Tempered glass is a kind of safety glass regularly used in applications in which standard glass could pose a potential danger. Tempered glass is four to five times stronger than float glass. The brittle nature of tempered glass causes it to shatter into small oval-shaped pebbles when broken. This eliminates the danger of sharp edges. Due to this property, along with its strength, tempered glass is often referred to as safety glass.Tempered glass is manufactured through a process of extreme heating and rapid cooling, making it harder than normal glass.<br />\nWhat can do the Tempered Glass?<br />\nBe used in laminated glass (ESG)<br />\nBe used in insulated glass<br />\nClear Float Tempered Glass;   Reflective Tempered Glass;   Tinted Tempered Glass; <br />\nLow-E Tempered Glass;      Tempered Pattern Glass;     Silk Screen Printed Tempered Glass<br />\n</p>','2,14',0,'0000-00-00',1,0,0,''),(241,'Laminated Glass (1)','https://member.asianproducts.com/images/pmimage/6/P13680658278724309m.jpg?1368066115',241,'<p>What is Laminated Glass ?<br />\nLaminated glass is a kind of safety glass that holds together when shattered. In the event of breaking, it is held in place by an interlayer, typically of polyvinyl butyral (PVB), between its two or more layers of glass. The interlayer keeps the layers of glass bonded even when broken, and its high strength prevents the glass from breaking up into large sharp pieces. This produces a characteristic \"spider web\" cracking pattern when the impact is not enough to completely pierce the glass.<br />\nWhat can do Laminated Glass ?<br />\nOften laminated glass is required to provide protection against man-made threats or natural disasters such as:<br />\n…Hurricanes, <br />\n…Bomb Blasts <br />\n…Bullet-Proof<br />\n…Forcible-entry.<br />\n…UV light<br />\n…Fire-proof<br />\n…Against Noise<br />\n…Floor Panels<br />\nLaminated Glass Combination<br />\nLaminated glass is available in various forms for commercial glazing applications. To provide a wide array of design options, as well as meet various performance levels, <br />\nClear Laminated Glass (CLG)(VSG)        Tinted Laminated Glass (TLG)<br />\nReflected Laminated Glass (RLG)          Patterned Laminated Glass (PLG)<br />\nUltra Clear Laminated Glass (UCLG)       Tempered Laminated Glass (ESG)<br />\nHeat-Proof Laminated Glass (HPLG)        Bullet-Proof Laminated Glass (BPLG)<br />\nDecorative Laminated Glass (DLG)         High Strength Laminated Glass (HSLG)<br />\nLink Glass offers its PVB interlayer in four standard thicknesses: 0.38 mm (015\"), 0.76mm (.030\") ,1.14mm (.045”) and 1.52 mm (.060\"). If a stronger, more durable laminated unit is required, Tempered Glass, Heat-Strengthened Glass is recommended. <br />\n</p>','2,14',0,'0000-00-00',1,0,0,''),(242,'Borosilicate Glass (9)','https://member.asianproducts.com/images/pmimage/6/P13680813244716787m.jpg?1368081619',242,'<p>What’s the Heat Resistant Glass<br />\nHeat Resistant Glass is one kind of Silicate Glass that has more resistance to thermal shock than ordinary glass,it can work under a certain temperature and pressure and special medium like acid liquor or alkali lye.<br />\nCharacteristics:	<br />\n1)	low thermal expansion coefficient,<br />\n2)	more resistance to thermal shock than ordinary glass<br />\n3)	high pressure resistant<br />\nApplication:<br />\nIndustrial boiler;valve;pipeline sight glass; metallurgical industry;chemical industry;oil industry;aviation industry;electric power industry,etc.<br />\nHeat Resistant Glass can be watch window in the high temperature furnace normally,it can work under the temperature:450℃,750℃,1200℃,1700℃,etc.<br />\n1)  Heat Resistant Glass for 300℃:it has high resistance to high temperature and pressure with lower price,at the same time it has high light transmittance,it can work under the 300℃.<br />\n2)  Heat Resistant Glass for 450℃:it can work perfectly under 450℃,the moment temperature can reach 520℃.light transmittance＜90%,bending strenth＜1100kgs/cm2,hydraulic strenth:25kg/cm2 under normally temperature and -25℃.the line expansion coefficient(20～300℃)3.3x10-6K-1<br />\n3） Heat Resistant Glass for 760℃:thermal stability(cool←→heat):△T860℃;safety for resistance to high temperature＜1000℃;<br />\nChemical Performance:	<br />\nwater resistance:ISO0719/DIN12111:HGB1;<br />\nacid resistance:ISO1776/DIN12116:min3;	<br />\nalkali resistance:ISO0695/DIN52322:A2. 		<br />\nSpecification size:1954mmx1100mm. color:bronze,clear,brown.<br />\n4)  Heat Resistant Glass for 1200℃:it can work for long time under 1200℃,it also work for short time under 1450℃.thermal expansion coefficient:5.5x10-7℃.it can bear huge range of temperature,it has 10,000 times insulation property than float glass.visible light transmittance＞93%,<br />\nthe Heat Resistant Glass can be used to semi-conductor,optical instrument,laboratory instrument,electrocity equipment,medicine equipment,chemical instrument,etc.<br />\nStandard:HG/T2144-91,HGJ501-86-0 (China);DIN52313-78(Germany)<br />\n</p>','2,14',0,'0000-00-00',1,0,0,''),(243,'laminated glass (1)','https://member.asianproducts.com/images/pmimage/6/P13680664450321134m.jpg?1368073695',243,'<p>Laminated glass is a kind of safety glass that holds together when shattered. In the event of breaking, it is held in place by an interlayer, typically of polyvinyl butyral (PVB), between its two or more layers of glass. The interlayer keeps the layers of glass bonded even when broken, and its high strength prevents the glass from breaking up into large sharp pieces. This produces a characteristic \"spider web\" cracking pattern when the impact is not enough to completely pierce the glass.</p>','2,14',0,'0000-00-00',1,0,0,''),(244,'DUO glass teapot (70356)','https://member.asianproducts.com/images/pmimage/6/P13680886746289267m.jpg?1368088843',244,'<p>DUO glass teapot</p>','2,